# Crazy Factory cron example
# Review before use.
# This is intentionally not installed automatically.
#
# The mission loop is the guarded entrypoint: it honors stop/pause/blocked/
# satisfied flags, detects stalls, runs one tick when safe, and writes
# reports/MISSION_STATUS.md. It never loops internally; cron supplies the beat.
#
# */30 * * * * cd /path/to/crazy_factory && python3 scripts/mission_loop.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1
#
# To pause/stop/unblock from a shell:
#   touch state/pause.flag    # pause (remove the file to resume)
#   touch state/stop.flag     # stop
#   rm -f state/blocked.flag  # clear a recovery block after fixing the cause
#
# Lower-level single tick (no flag/stall/satisfaction guard):
# */30 * * * * cd /path/to/crazy_factory && ./bin/factory-tick >> logs/cron.log 2>&1
